# 🔒 PDF Redaction API (YOLO + OCR)

A production-ready API that automatically redacts sensitive information from PDFs by:

* 👤 Detecting & masking faces using YOLOv8
* 🔢 Detecting & masking Aadhaar numbers using OCR (Tesseract)
* 📄 Returning a fully redacted PDF

---

## 🚀 Features

* Upload PDF via API
* Face detection using YOLO model
* Aadhaar number masking using OCR
* Secure API key authentication
* Returns processed PDF directly
* Partially deployable over local machine and later can be live using port forwarding like ngrok or cloudflare 
* If need to deploy over cloud -need good GPU, RAM, Processing and CPU. (Cloud like AWS, GCP, Render etc)

---

## 🧠 Project Architecture

```
Client Request
    ↓
FastAPI Endpoint (/mask-pdf)
    ↓
PDF → Images (pdf2image)
    ↓
YOLO Face Detection + Masking
    ↓
OCR Aadhaar Detection + Masking
    ↓
Rebuild PDF
    ↓
Return Masked PDF
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
project/
│
├── main.py                # FastAPI app (main backend)
├── requirements.txt       # Python dependencies
├── README.md              # Project documentation
└── yolov8n-face.pt        # Available in this repository
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation (Local)

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/aryapathakxii/Masking_Project/API.git
cd API
```

---

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

### 3. Install System Dependencies

#### Windows/Localhost

# 3.1: Download Poppler (Used to convert pdf into images)
Poppler (for pdf2image)
Download from: https://github.com/oschwartz10612/poppler-windows
(download .zip file and unzip it in C drive and mention the path in your code for windows user)
Set path in code:

from pdf2image import convert_from_path
poppler_path = r"C:\poppler\poppler-25.12.0\Library\bin"
pages_1 = convert_from_path(r"D:\AFPL_Project_ML\ML_Interview_Material\test_set.pdf", poppler_path=poppler_path)

# 3.2: Download Tesseract OCR (Used to detect text in the image and mask it as per defined pattern)
Tesseract OCR
Download from: https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract
(download .zip file and unzip it in C drive and mention the path in your code for windows user)
Set path in code:

import pytesseract
pytesseract.pytesseract.tesseract_cmd = r"C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\tesseract.exe"

---

### 4. Run API

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

---

### 5. Open Swagger UI

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/mask-pdf
```

---

## 🔑 API Usage

### Endpoint:

```
POST /mask-pdf
```

### Headers:

```
x-api-key: mysecret12122000
```

---

### Python Example:

```python
    import requests

    url = "http://127.0.0.1:8000/mask-pdf"
    headers = {"x-api-key":"mysecret12122000"}
    files = {"file": open("development_set.pdf","rb")}
    r = requests.post(url, headers=headers, files=files)
    with open("output.pdf","wb") as f:
        f.write(r.content)
    print("Masked PDF saved!")
```

---

## 🤖 Model Handling

* The YOLO face detection model is stored in the repository

```python
MODEL_PATH = "yolov8n-face.pt"
```

